    =========================================================
    Candidate Sharing & Collaboration Dashboard Page — AI Shortlist Review
    Updated intent based on feedback:
      This page is scoped to a specific role. Candidates listed were AI‑shortlisted. The recruiter reviews each candidate via a right‑side preview, can open the full profile, and selects the ones to share onward. Manager feedback sits below as a Jira‑style thread.

    OECs (Objective & Experience Criteria):
      1) Task success: Recruiter can select ≥1 candidate and send a note in < 20s without errors.
      2) Visibility: Confirmation banner appears within 300ms; selected count visible at all times.
      3) Comprehension: ≥80% of users correctly identify Share as the active tab.
      4) Efficiency: Share button disabled until valid inputs; avoids accidental sends.
      5) Accessibility: Labels for controls; focus states; minimum 4.5:1 contrast for body text.
      6) New: First candidate auto‑selected with preview visible on load.

    Testing approach (no execution required):
      - Heuristic review (Nielsen 10) focusing on visibility, feedback, error prevention.
      - 5‑minute usability walk‑through: ask user to review preview, approve selections, and share.
      - DevTools trace: verify checkbox → selected state; preview render; banner animation.

    Versioning/JSFiddle: Paste this file into JSFiddle/CodePen as a single page (HTML only).
    =========================================================
  -->

